Event(s):	BUD (Budapest-Lorinc) * LATITUDE: 47.429100 * LONGITUDE: 19.182200 * ELEVATION: 139.1 m * LOCATION: Hungary, Budapest * METHOD/DEVICE: Monitoring station (MONS) * COMMENT: BSRN Station no: 14; Surface type: grass; Topography type: flat, rural; Horizon: doi:10.1594/PANGAEA.931862; Station scientist: Dénes Fekete (fekete.d@met.hu)
Comment:	The upward measurements are recorded on a different data logger than the other parameters. This data logger failed in April and after the replacement, not all programs were synchronized, so the elementary samples were lost, only the 10-min average values remained. This error was only discovered at the end of September, when it was resolved, so only from October on the file again contains the data from the upward measurements.
